				<div class="comment-body"><blockquote><p>&#8230;believing that I hadn’t read enough eligible books in any particular calendar year to make my opinions valid&#8230;</p></blockquote>
<p>The only quantity that isn&#8217;t enough is zero. We address this matter in the <a href="../../../ask-a-question/comment-page-1/index.php?page_id=5" title="Hugo Awards FAQ" rel="nofollow">Hugo Awards FAQ</a>:</p>
<blockquote><p>If you have seen just one movie or read one story that you think is good enough to deserve a Hugo, you should nominate it. The Hugos work best when as many fans as possible use their own experience to nominate and vote for the things they think are wonderful.</p></blockquote>
<p>Members who disqualify themselves because &#8220;I don&#8217;t read/see/watch everything that came out last year, so I&#8217;m Not Worthy&#8221; are doing themselves and the Awards a disservice. Vote <em>your</em> preferences without worrying about what else is out there.</p>
</div>

