				<div class="comment-body"><p>And William, Kevin&#8217;s point is precisely that if you give in to this feeling, you&#8217;re Letting The Bad Guys Win &#8212; and I am deliberately refraining from pointing at any particular side when I say that phrase because the identification itself is immaterial. The point behind such &#8220;scorched earth&#8221; tactics is to win by making everyone else leave. A more rational  response is to have more voices, not fewer, making the sample size more statistically significant, so the result can more reliably echo the views of the whole.</p>
</div>

