				<div class="comment-body"><p>This is my first comment on this thread. As some of you may recognise by my name, I have been involved in SF Fandom since 1977, and have helped RUN worldcons. I DETEST the characterization of the Sick Puppies as Cheats or that their noiminations ammounted to corruption. They saw a loophole in the rules and capitalized on it. This is no differerent than a Min/Max Gamer. There is only one rule for those who nominate and vote for the Hugo Awards that Should be ABSOLUTE.</p>
<p> Nominate and vote for those Items that in their opinion DESERVE THE AWARD.</p>
<p> Period.<br />
 Fandom should be accepting, not exclusive. Hate should not be part of our fannish vocabulary. We are supposed to be the safe haven for the strange, odd, and misfits.</p>
